author: djames
msg: Only clean generated SWIG files when we are in non-release mode. This change
allows developers to clean generated SWIG files using "make clean", without
needing to use the "extraclean-swig-py" rules.
* Makefile.in
(clean-swig-headers): Only clean headers when we are in non-release mode.
(extraclean-swig-headers, extraclean-swig-py, extraclean-swig-rb,
extraclean-swig-pl): Remove.
(clean-swig-pl, clean-swig-rb): Only remove generated *.c files when we are
in non-release mode.
(clean-swig-py): Only remove generated *.c and *.py files when we are in
non-release mode. Remove *.pyc files from build directory.
* build/generator/gen_make.py
(write): Output "RELEASE_MODE = 1" when we are in release mode. Remove
extraclean-swig rule.

author: lundblad
msg: On wc-propcaching branch: Merge r17324:r17402 from trunk.

author: maxb
msg: SWIG build and clean rules tidyup.
* Makefile.in (local-extraclean): Add extraclean-swig.
(clean-swig): Remove rule, it is provided by generator.
* build/generator/gen_make.py: Strip out much of the complex and very verbose
clean rule handling in favour of simple rules using wildcards, already
added to Makefile.in in previous commits.
Also, stop copying .i files to the builddir unnecessarily, just refer to
them in the source dir.
